About US

North South Consulting Group, LLC (NSCG) is an Economically Disadvantaged, Woman-Owned, Service-Disabled, and Veteran-Owned small business recognized for its commitment to excellence and integrity in service.

NSCG supports contracts and consulting efforts on a national level. Through the combination of extensive DoD relationships, technical expertise, successful and ongoing contract past performance, creativity, and innovation, NSCG provides a value-based approach to clients and partners powered by efficient service delivery options. We work closely with the U.S. Military community to enable and staff talent throughout the United States and its territories using a corporate staff of Military Veterans, and our commitment to excellence that guides all corporate initiatives.

NSCG at a Glance

Founded: 2012

Headquarters: Elizabethtown, KY

Dynamic Solutions in a Fast-Paced, Always Changing Environment

The NSCG Team embraces change and provides real-time solutions to solve the human resources, professional and technical needs of Government organizations.

Real-time Solutions and Involved Leadership

Our team is involved at the beginning of each contract, and stays involved throughout the contract period of performance. We believe in talent management as a way to improve processes both in the short and long term.

North South Consulting Group, LLC

NSCG provides over three decades of Military experience paired with solid small business past performance both in public and private service sectors. Our senior management and contracting experience paired with the flexibility of a small business is applied to provide our clients and partners with efficient, tangible results. Through a multi-level, analysis driven methodology that leverages critical details into overarching strategy, we ensure clients and partners receive consistent, dependable results. Our core competencies include but are not limited to:

Research and Analysis Call and Contact Center Operations Interpreter Services Digital-Social Media Strategic Development, Management and Outreach Casualty and Mortuary Affairs Operations Military and Veteran Case Management and Claims Processing Non-medical Case Management Military Human Resources Organizational Refinement/Resource Optimization Training Development Military Recruiting Military IT Support/Help Desk
